We also recommended that the Municipal Accountant prepare and record JEV upon receipt of DVs and supporting documents to adjust and correct balances of the affected accounts in the FS.

We recommended that Management strengthen internal control in granting CAs in accordance with Sections 2.2 and 8 of COA Circular nos. 96-004 and 97-002, respectively.  Likewise, on the part of the officials and employees concerned, we recommended strict compliance with Section 3.1.2.1 of COA Circular 96-004 on the rules and regulations on liquidation of CAs.

Specifically, we recommended that the MA:

 Require employees to settle first their previous CAs for travel before additional CAs will be granted;

Strictly monitor the settlement of unliquidated balance of ₱328,609;

Send final demand letter to concerned personnel requiring immediate liquidation/settlement of their unliquidated CAs;

Update SLs relative to CAs; and

Prepare necessary documents relative to the unliquidated CAs subject for write-off from the books of accounts and submit the same to COA.

We recommended that the LCE require:

The AMT to prepare Loan Repayment Vouchers based on the amortization table provided by MDFO to avoid overpayment of interest;

The MA to reconcile with MDFO records and request that the amount of ₱121,199 be applied as debit to the loan principal, otherwise the overpayment shall be borne personally by persons found liable thereto.

